Two elderly women sustained serious injuries after a light motor vehicle crashed into a wall at the underground parking at a mall in Rosebank on Monday.Netcare911 paramedics stated that both women were occupants of the vehicle.Netcare911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said while assessing the injured it was found that the elderly woman was in a serious but stable condition and the other woman sustained moderate injuries&#8221;.Mathe stated that both women were stabilised on scene and transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care.The cause of the accident is still unknown.&nbsp;-Aviwe Maxheke&nbsp;&nbsp;